{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49/comments/52460787.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49#comment-52460787"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 49, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "title": "Subprocess deadlock with multiple threads"}, "content": {"raw": null, "markup": "markdown", "html": "", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-06-05T22:52:00.718001+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 52460787}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49/comments/52460790.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49#comment-52460790"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 49, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "title": "Subprocess deadlock with multiple threads"}, "content": {"raw": null, "markup": "markdown", "html": "", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-06-05T22:52:33.452216+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 52460790}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49/comments/52476009.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49#comment-52476009"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 49, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "title": "Subprocess deadlock with multiple threads"}, "content": {"raw": "OK, it looks like this is because on unix, the `multiprocessing` module `fork()`s new processes by default, and the M-LOOP Gaussian Process uses a `multiprocessing.Process` for its `Learner()` class. The other learners use a thread.\n\nHowever, zmq is *not* fork-safe. So zmq is breaking at some random point in the future after the fork. I guess I'm surprised it works for even a short time before crashing.\n\nAnyway, the solution is not to fork. In Python \u2265 3.4 one can do `multiprocessing.set_start_method('spawn')`. So I'll make it do that.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>OK, it looks like this is because on unix, the <code>multiprocessing</code> module <code>fork()</code>s new processes by default, and the M-LOOP Gaussian Process uses a <code>multiprocessing.Process</code> for its <code>Learner()</code> class. The other learners use a thread.</p>\n<p>However, zmq is <em>not</em> fork-safe. So zmq is breaking at some random point in the future after the fork. I guess I'm surprised it works for even a short time before crashing.</p>\n<p>Anyway, the solution is not to fork. In Python \u2265 3.4 one can do <code>multiprocessing.set_start_method('spawn')</code>. So I'll make it do that.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-06-06T20:31:54.799444+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 52476009}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49/comments/52505791.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49#comment-52505791"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 49, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "title": "Subprocess deadlock with multiple threads"}, "content": {"raw": "Force multiprocessing to spawn new processes instead of forking them on >= 3.4.\n\nThis fixes issue #49 which was caused by forking, but zeromq not being fork-safe.\n\n\u2192 <<cset 7930cddcab0c>>", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Force multiprocessing to spawn new processes instead of forking them on &gt;= 3.4.</p>\n<p>This fixes issue <a href=\"#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/49/subprocess-deadlock-with-multiple-threads\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Subprocess deadlock with multiple threads\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#49</s></a> which was caused by forking, but zeromq not being fork-safe.</p>\n<p>\u2192 &lt;&lt;cset <a href=\"#!/labscript_suite/lyse/commits/7930cddcab0c\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">7930cddcab0c</a>&gt;&gt;</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-06-09T16:37:11.914852+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 52505791}], "page": 1, "size": 4}